      "body" : "I think this is exactly a no-op. The internal result from CreateNewBlock is incorrectly computed (the sigop value for the coinbase transaction is off by a factor 4), however, this value is ignored by all call sites:\r\n* GBT lets the consumer construct their own coinbase, so does not report anything about the temporary coinbase transaction used inside CreateNewBlock\r\n* The `generate` RPC call uses the constructed block directly, ignoring all metadata about it.",
      "created_at" : "2016-07-19T11:07:59Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/8362#issuecomment-233600683",
